The paper describes a search system for social science information that integrates and links different types of information, including research data sets, publications, survey variables, questions from questionnaires, survey instruments, and tools. This work involves information retrieval (IR) techniques for searching and linking information, digital library (DL) technologies for organizing and managing information, database (DB) systems for storing and querying data, cybersecurity (CY) for protecting sensitive data, and social informatics (SI) for studying the social aspects of information use. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories are cs.IR, cs.DL, and cs.DB, followed by cs.CY and cs.SI.
